@page "/"
@using SkiaSharp
@using SkiaSharp.Views.Blazor

<h1>Issue #1902 Repro</h1>
<SKCanvasView OnPaintSurface="OnPaintSurface" style="width:800px;height:600px;" />

@code {
    private void OnPaintSurface(SKPaintSurfaceEventArgs e)
    {
        var canvas = e.Surface.Canvas;
        canvas.Clear(SKColors.White);
        var fontFamily = "Tahoma";
        var typeFace = SKTypeface.FromFamilyName(fontFamily, SKFontStyle.BoldItalic);
        Console.WriteLine($"REPRO: Requested '{fontFamily}', got '{typeFace.FamilyName}'");
        Console.WriteLine($"REPRO: Match={fontFamily == typeFace.FamilyName}");
        using SKPaint paint = new() { Style = SKPaintStyle.Fill, TextSize = 26, IsAntialias = true, Typeface = typeFace, Color = SKColors.Black };
        canvas.DrawText($"Requested: {fontFamily}", 30, 40, paint);
        canvas.DrawText($"Got: {typeFace.FamilyName}", 30, 80, paint);
        canvas.DrawText("Fancy Text", 30, 130, paint);
        Console.WriteLine($"SUCCESS: rendered {e.Info.Width}x{e.Info.Height}");
    }
}

proposedResponse.body:
Thanks for reporting this. We've confirmed the behavior: `SKTypeface.FromFamilyName()` always returns the default bundled font (Noto Mono) in Blazor WASM, regardless of the requested font family.

This is a **WASM platform limitation**, not a SkiaSharp bug. In the WASM sandbox, Skia's font manager has no access to system or browser fonts — it can only resolve fonts bundled into the WASM binary. Since only Noto Mono is bundled by default, all `FromFamilyName()` lookups fall back to it.

**Tested:**
| Environment | Result |
|---|---|
| Blazor WASM (SkiaSharp 3.119.2) | ❌ Returns 'Noto Mono' for all font families |
| Blazor WASM (main branch) | ❌ Same behavior |
| Console macOS (SkiaSharp 3.119.2) | ✅ Correctly resolves Tahoma, Arial, etc. |

**Workaround:** Load fonts explicitly using `SKTypeface.FromStream()` or `SKTypeface.FromData()`:

```csharp
// Option 1: Embedded resource
using var stream = typeof(MyApp).Assembly
    .GetManifestResourceStream("MyApp.Fonts.Tahoma.ttf");
var typeface = SKTypeface.FromStream(stream);

// Option 2: Fetch from server (enables browser caching)
var fontBytes = await httpClient.GetByteArrayAsync("/fonts/Tahoma.ttf");
using var data = SKData.CreateCopy(fontBytes);
var typeface = SKTypeface.FromData(data);
```

For best performance, load fonts once at startup and reuse the `SKTypeface` instance rather than reloading on each paint call.
